{{Infobox Artwork | image_file=Aparici%C3%B3n_de_la_Virgen_del_Pilar_a_Santiago_y_a_sus_disc%C3%ADpulos_zaragozanos.jpg | title=Apparition of the Virgin of the Pillar to Saint James and his Saragossan disciples | other_language_1=[[Spanish language|Spanish]] | other_title_1=Aparición de la Virgen del Pilar a Santiago y a sus discípulos zaragozanos | artist=[[Francisco Goya]] | year=1768-1769 | medium=Oil on canvas | height_metric=79 | width_metric=55 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | museum=Private Collection | city= }}
'''''Apparition of the Virgin of the Pillar to Saint James and his Saragossan disciples''''' is a 1768-69 painting by [[Francisco de Goya]]. It shows the [[Virgin of the Pillar]] apparition. It is the only painting by Goya ever to have been exhibited in Goya's birthplace, on 14 January 1996.
